      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.hubeali": [
          "Ali Bin Ibrahim, from his father, from Amro Bin Usman, from Al Mufazzal Bin Salih, from Zayd Al Shahaam, ",
          "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> having been asked about hunting the fish, and if he has not Named (<span class=\"iTxt\">Bismillah</span>) over it. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem with it, if it was alive and he seizes it’."
        ],
        "en.sarwar": [
          "2. Ali ibn Ibrahim has narrated from his father from ‘Amr ibn ‘Uthman from al-Mufaddal ibn Salih from Zayd al-Shahham who has said the following: “Once abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, was asked about catching fish without a mention of the name of Allah. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not unlawful if it is alive when he catches it.’” "
        ]
      }
